one_reviews_text: You get one track and its pretty much the perfect track for a single experience, well put together and runs like a dream, its such a shame the user cant input their own music and have all the hard work that the dev put in as a visualizer! I do recommend this however.

review_title: Other designers and musicians take note
one_reviews_text: If you design for VR or work on soundtracks for VR games or experiences, take note of this app. This hits all the marks for a great experience in virtual reality. The visuals are well optimized, so there seems to be nothing lacking in the graphics. They work very well with the excellent soundtrack. This experience is over rather quickly, but I know for sure that I'll return to it often because the music is unlikely to get old. I hope to see more from this designer and hear more from this producer.

What a beautifully-crafted mix of audio-visual delights. Outstanding; thank you very very much; I'm slowly going blind from glaucoma, so believe me I really appreciate seeing something as beautiful as this. xxxxxx
Please make more :)

I downloaded this a while ago because it was free so I didn't know what to expect, but I ended up loving it when I finally decided to give it a go. It's very relaxing. Just sit back and enjoy the music and the light show. It isn't the kind of music that I listen to, but I ended up playing it again and again. It's very unique and a great VR experience
This types of things remind me why I love humanity.

Just sit down and enjoy this fantastic audiovisual journey. I wish there would be more VR experience like this. But you need good headphones!!! 

Since I use the Rift S with it's kind of speakers, I really get angry about FB when I want to enjoy this app.  And whit my 2.1 speakers to much immersion get lost. The speakers of the CV1 have been pretty good. So why??? Market analyses?Much immersion comes even from the sound. 

But sorry, I forgot myself... 
I would give 6 stars this smooth floating trip! Please more ;)
was amazing
wow just wow that was amazing ! best vr sofar

review_title: Best Light/Graphic to music in VR
one_reviews_text: Love the whole 4-5 minute display to electronic I've ever seen. More Please! - I curate Spotify songs then create pllaylists. Like ''Above & Beyond', ''ZHU', 'Eli & Fur', 'Zedd', 'Calvin Harris' etc... Would like a tool to create light shows that go to the music. Steam Wallpaper Engine has a few people who have made some wallpaper reactive to sound. GREAT JOB! If you created something that would react to users music like Spotify, Id be the first to buy!

being well in to my 50's, i found the music enjoyable.  the visual experience was fantastic.  i would have paid $1 for this, so charge a $1, and like butters said, make some MFing money!  :-)

just stand there, listen to the music, and look around.

i would like to see more of these kinds of VR experiences.

To me, and I rarely write review at all if any, this is an exemplary representation of VR and what it is capable of in creating a world beyond the reality. This art shows how VR could be different than other mediums and the height it could take one into a totally surealistic dream land. Remarkable work and certainly a representational effort in VR.

p.s. hope the developer would continue extending this piece of art

Just look around and listen to the music, nothing to do - it's like a music video, just with an artificial world.
The musis is great, starting slowly and growing - and the environment changes into a perfect matching light show - starting nearly black and minimalistic and growing with the music. More such stuff! I would even pay, seen it multiple times already.
Only problem: The Rift S "black" level (more like medium gray) destroys some of the looks in the darker scenes. But the app can nothing for this.
Beautiful, just let yourself go.

This is not virtual reality, it's irreality - and it's beautiful. You need to like that kind of electronic music, but even if not, the visuals are beautiful to look at and let you flow through a fictive space of something. Imporvement idea: I would wish the sequences were longer, or that once could choose the place to look at. Maybe add more of this kind, because it's just wonderful.

Without attempting to sound pretentious, this is a VR attempt at the visual presentation of the symbiosis of music—and it’s quite good. I would love to hear more music combined with more visual explorations. Classical adaptations would be fantastic in this format, much in the fashion that Forest of Piano makes accessible the intricacies of the piano for idiots like me who don’t know anything about music or art.

Pretty much what the demo scene would look like in VR, however the music/visuals are pretty average. But it is free, so little reason not to check it out, especially if you are into this kind of stuff.

its not as "wow factor" to me as the screenshots indicate.   starts off rather dark and quite honestly a lot of the time the spaces are rather dark visualizations are interesting but could have been better.   not bad for a free demo but not quite the "wow" factor i was hoping for.

review_title: I haven't been in a Disco bar in years!

Title says it all. Nothing to do but watch for around 10-15 minutes, but wow! Slow few stars moving start that just keeps building and starts you moving through a pretty spectacular light show. Way too short to pay for, but you know, you don't, it's free! If they added more cool content and charged a small fee, like $1.99 U.S., I would pay for it. Not worth a big title cost but with a good hour or more of this amazing visual zen ride, I'd push a little money their way. Keep going developer(s)!!!

review_title: To chill after a day at work
one_reviews_text:
I like the idea; you turn on music and something happen; it is fundamentally the equivalent of the visualization plugins in winamp (you may not be that old to remember that :) ).
The music type change the type of animations and their speed; decently accurated and nicely done. If you want a relaxing experience for your VR session, then this is your app.
Really capture the spirit of the dark-club-bright-lights experience. Thumping soundtrack really heightens the imersiveness of the experience. I'd readily pay money for more of this!!
wow... just wish there was binaural sound to match it, would increase immersion of these 3d music vids :)

review_title: You will enter a different place
one_reviews_text: Wow, what an experience. The music, the setting, the movement, it all blends into one fantastic experience which felt smooth but very much like a real place in some incomprehensible way. Try this out, then watch it again dozens of times and show it to all your friends. That's what I did!
Great idea well put together, love to see more.

Does exactly what it sets to accomplish. If you like electronic music, it's a great one-time track to bob your head to. I see potential for a full game, where you could create your own soundscape to a track with G-mod type tools.
The future of music VR is here.  Very nice experience and look forward to more music journeys with VR capabilities. A nice app to showcase VR to your friends.
By far the best music experience I have had in VR.
WHAT MORE CAN I SAY, PURE CHILL,, I ONLY WISH IT WAS LONGER AND MORE TUNES TO PLAY

This was absolutely sick, I totally was not expecting something so amazing when I downloaded this. The execution of lighting in this experience is simply amazing, yet somehow they make white on a black background not completely kill your eyes. The music is fantastic and the experience as a whole is stunning. Well done guys!
A beautiful  and  mesmerizing experience
I love showing this off to people. I find myself occasionally going back to this app just becasue it's so chill

You just CANNOT give this 1 star or even 2 or 3. It is absoultely mind blowing light show, worth waiting for 2 hours in line in some kind of amusement park after paying price of admission, except this is for FREE in comfort of your own home and you can "ride it" as many times as you please!

review_title: Great experience to just chill to
one_reviews_text: I've only played this for a short period, but the concept is awesome. The execution of syncing trance and house music to geometric stimulae is well done and not overwhelming. Coupling in that you can use your own music, well, you can literally create a visual experience for your favorite chill playlist. My only disgust with this, and hence 4 stars, is the in-app purchases. While not overly expensive, I have always felt this business model hurts more than it helps in the long run.

N'to and also the other guys from hungry music are just brilliant! Epic techno! Beside the point of the very well chosen soundtrack, this app affords a beautiful and immersive "proof of concept" for VR music visualisation. Well done!
Kind of think I might pick up doing drugs again, if only this was longer. Not so long That it would promote drug addictions!!!

Be completely surrounded by spectacular shapes and worlds that pulse and flare and burst perfectly in time with the beat.

I would pay for more of these!

Absolutely incredible experience and one that blows the socks off your friends if they've never tried VR! If you're an electro fan then get ready for the ride of your life! And even if you're not, you'll love it just the same ;)
A beautiful experience. Great track, great visuals. If there was in-app donate for a buck, it'd give it as a tip/donation.

review_title: Great VR experience with huge potentual
one_reviews_text: This starts off a bit slow but is an amazing "ride" definitly worth experiencing.  Id like to see the core idea/technology made into an app that lets you pick your own music and one of several environment types and plays the song with the environment morphing and moving to the beat that it maps out from it's length and pattern.  If I ever see that app for a reasonable price, it'll be a must-buy for me.
Really cool and immersive expereince. Music and visuals are just awesome, I want more things like this.

review_title: One of my favorite VR experiences
one_reviews_text: This VR experience has hands down been one of my favorites with all VR content combined.  It's extremly fun to watch this once before bed each night, as I find it leads to some amazing dreams.  The music is beautiful, the colors bring you to a new fantasy world, and the relaxing waves of patterns are just an absolute delite to the eyes.  I absolutely look forward to seeing more content like this, and find it a treat in itself to consider the possibilites for VR with true experiences like this coming to life.
Good music and amazing visuals. I was blown away by how cool it was. Idk why anyone would give it less than 4 stars
This demo brought me back to the 90's when I was always viewing demoscenos demos from the Amiga and PC. Great scenes that are in sync with the audio.
Excellent and free!

Great execution of visuals, music and experience. Sit back, relax and watch and feel the beat. It's amazing made, the lights, the effects, the beat... wished it would be much much longer, maybe offering even more sound tracks and "journeys" - I'll call them so, because this is what it kinda is, a musical journey. You forget everything around you with this!
Yes it is a nice app but there are no interactive action. You can just pause and continue it with touch controllers. It is better to be short this way, otherwise you will get bored.
An amazing trip, especially for those who loves eletronic music. You can sit or lay on the ground while enjoy your trip.

A surrealistic geometrical world with amazing graphics all together with this amazing tune. The only interaction is push to start and pause/play. It's cool how when you pause, the music and motion stops, but some the effects (like the fog) keep moving so you still feel like the world you're in is still alive.  Does contain some artificial locomotion, but it's gentle and I didn't experience any nausea. Definitely worth the try.

I'd give 9 out of 10....Absolute tune from start to finish.  Good visuals.  Smoke effect is good.  Reflections good.  Fire ok.  A great experience.  I love these audio/visual apps.  This is probably still the best on Oculus.
